{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, GenAI can automatically create meeting notes with realtime transcription, provide meeting summaries, or extract information from videos.",
    "Existing tools such as Otter, Supernormal, or Colibri can be used in conjunction with online collaboration tools such as MS Teams or Zoom to process and analyze every spoken word.",
    "Notably, extracted tacit knowledge can be reintegrated into existing feedback loops, enabling the AI model to continuously learn and reducing the need for human-in-the-loop processes (Brea & Ford, 2023).",
    "GenAI can identify insights not readily apparent to human decision makers to serve as stimuli for novel ideas, encouraging employees to explore new avenues and innovations (Brea & Ford, 2023; Haefner et al., 2021).",
    "For instance, in the pharmaceutical and material science industry, GenAI can be used to analyze data from scientific literature, patents, and databases, and propose new chemical compounds or materials with desirable properties (Lee et al., 2023; Ni et al., 2023)."
  ]
}